commitResults.messageTitle: Add emoji to greeting in SumTingWong.java
Improve on the skeletal version of Sumtingwong
commitResults.messageBody: Sumtingwong now echos commands entered by the user, and exits when the user types the command "bye"

commitResults.messageTitle: Add ability to store text in SumTingWong.java
commitResults.messageBody: Add the ability to store whatever text entered by the user and display them back to the user when requested.
Modified SumTingWong.java to make use of Task objects
Add the ability to mark tasks as done in SumTingWong.java and change the status back to not done

commitResults.messageTitle: Add markAsDone() and markAsUndone() methods to Task.java
Add basic error handling for ToDO, Event and Deadline
Added support for deleting tasks in SumTingWong.java
commitResults.messageBody: Updated SumTingWong to use ArrayLists to store task objects instead of primitive arrays

Add a saveTasks method to TaskManager.java to save an arrayList of tasks into a TaskList.txt file

saveTasks checks whether the data file and the TaskList.txt exists in the first place.
If not, it will create the ./data/ directory and the TaskList.txt file.

Add a function fromFileFormat() in Task.java to support the loadTasks()
function. fromFileFormat takes in a line from the TaskList.txt file,
reads the line and returns the correct Event, Deadline or Todo object
depending on what the task is.

Update constructor of Task.java to take in a boolean isDone param
to support the fromFileFormat() function.

Update ToDo.java, Deadline.java and Event.java to have their respective
toFileFormat() function which converts the event into a file format to
be stored in TaskList.txt

commitResults.messageTitle: Add support for java LocalDate and LocalTime
commitResults.messageBody:
Update Deadline.java to store the deadline as java.time.LocalDate and
java.time.LocalTime objects.

Update SumTingWong.java to accept dates in yyyy-mm-dd format
and print in MMM dd yyyy format
